{"TopicId":174463,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Autosave Disable Mod Request","CreatedByName":"Mark Kerbin","CreatedById":167193,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T21:18:14Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mark Kerbin","CreatedById":167193,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T21:18:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, first if anyone knows how to do this without a mod, please let me know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, I would very much like a mod that removes the autosave feature from flight and maybe the editor. Similar to that mod that forces an autosave after various important moments, only the exact opposite.\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuite frankly I think it is silly there is no way to turn off autosave\u00A0seeing as it causes my game to stutter every 5 or so seconds. I just need some way to kill it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nils277","CreatedById":122414,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T21:40:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think this is due to the autosave but the garbage collector when memory has to be cleared. See here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7530152152\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/168165-g\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:222px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe installing the mod \u003Cstrong\u003EMemgraph\u003C/strong\u003E as pointed out there will help you too. This problem may or\u00A0be caused by (too many) mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-30T21:41:40Z\u0022 title=\u002204/30/2018 09:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 30, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Nils277\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T22:59:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223368129\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525123094\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167193\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mark Kerbin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Mark Kerbin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright, first if anyone knows how to do this without a mod, please let me know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOpen the Settings.cfg file in your main KSP directory in a text editor and search for AUTOSAVE_INTERVAL and right below it is AUTOSAVE_SHORT_INTERVAL. I\u0027m guessing setting them both to 0 will stop the autosave from firing altogether\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mark Kerbin","CreatedById":167193,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-30T23:18:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223368214\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525129159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Drew Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Drew Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOpen the Settings.cfg file in your main KSP directory in a text editor and search for AUTOSAVE_INTERVAL and right below it is AUTOSAVE_SHORT_INTERVAL. I\u0027m guessing setting them both to 0 will stop the autosave from firing altogether\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat actually makes it fire constantly.\u00A0 And apparently -1 causes mayhem (reddit) so I\u0027m not giving that a go. =P\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-01T00:03:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223368236\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525130337\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167193\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Mark Kerbin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, Mark Kerbin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat actually makes it fire \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Econstantly\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suspected as much. Given there\u0027s no setting to turn it off, why would they code it so that a 0 interval does nothing? Oh well, worth a shot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-01T07:28:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223368145\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022174463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221525124440\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022122414\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nils277\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Nils277 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think this is due to the autosave but the garbage collector when memory has to be cleared. See here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1406571250\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/168165-g\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:226px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe installing the mod \u003Cstrong\u003EMemgraph\u003C/strong\u003E as pointed out there will help you too. This problem may or\u00A0be caused by (too many) mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince I\u0027m outa likes, I\u0027ll quote you here.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStuttering is most likely from garbage cleanup, not auto saves.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGet Memgraph and use it.\u00A0 RTM and it will speed the game up considerably.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}